 quasar and it also illuminates the emission-line bridge, suggests the\nquasar radiates isotropically and any obscuring torus is small. These results\ndemonstrate the power of MUSE for investigating the dynamics of interacting\nsystems at high redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jul 2015 20:00:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-30"}
