\\delta$ between a short and the long one. Only when\n$J^{\\prime\\prime}=J^\\prime$, their magnitudes become equal and the\nrelative-angles $120^\\circ$. This ${\\bf q}=(0,0)$ phase has the translational\nsymmetry of the Kagom\\'e lattice with isosceles triangular unit-cells. The\nratio of the intensities of certain Bragg peaks, $I_{(1,0)}/I_{(0,1)} =\n4\\sin^2{(\\frac{\\pi}{6}+\\delta)}$, presents an experimental measure of the\ndeviation, $\\delta$, from the $120^\\circ$ order.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jul 2015 07:06:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Aug 2017 16:53:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-29"}
